The 25th film in the odyssey that is the Marvel Cinematic Universe has arrived, and with it a breath of fresh air as we prepare for its Fourth Phase. Shang-Chi and The Legend of The Ten Rings is here, but was it any good? Join the guys at CBC as they dissect this new entry into the MCU, have a love fest over the fight scenes and applaud the return of character with a special place in our hearts! Remember if you aim at nothing you'll hit nothing so make sure you aim to listen to the episode and hit that subscribe button as we talk all things Shang-Chi! Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [ComicBookClique.com](episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media. Send us feedback at ComicBookClique@Gmail.com! You Are Worthy! Please [SUPPORT US ON PATREON](http://Patreon.com/CBCClubhouse)!

